  "response": "The correct phrase is \"Can you explain it to me?\" or \"Could you explain it to me?\" \n\nIn both cases, the word \"it\" refers to the subject being explained. The construction \"explain me\" is not standard English. You would typically use \"explain\" with a direct object that is either a concept or information you need clarification on.",
